																				<div class="sg-editor">
						
<p>You don’t have access to a gym? That’s not a problem. A full body bodyweight workout can build strength, boost endurance, and enhance mobility anytime, anywhere.</p>



<p><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/body-weight-exercises" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Bodyweight exercises</a> challenge your muscles using nothing but gravity and your body. They’re simple, effective, and perfect for every fitness level. Whether you’re new to exercise or looking for a fresh routine, bodyweight training fits into any lifestyle.</p>



<p>In this article, we’ll guide you through a range of exercises to target all major muscle groups in one workout. If you’re ready to transform your fitness and feel stronger in daily life, this workout is for you. Let’s explore the best bodyweight exercises for a stronger, healthier you.</p>



<div class="wp-block-group ft-snippet is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
<p class="has-medium-font-size">8 Moves For A Full Body Bodyweight Workout</p>



<p>This full body bodyweight workout builds strength, endurance, and functional fitness by targeting all major muscle groups. Incorporate them into your routine for a complete and effective workout:</p>



<ul>
<li><a href="#Push-Up">Push-Up.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Dip">Dip.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Plank">Plank.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Pull-Up">Pull-Up.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Squat">Squat.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Bodyweight-Single-Leg-Deadlift">Bodyweight Single-Leg Deadlift.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Mountain-Climber">Mountain Climber.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Burpee">Burpee.</a></li>
</ul>
</div></div>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio youtube-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe title="ULTIMATE FULL BODY WORKOUT AT HOME – GET FIT WITHOUT EQUIPMENT!" width="500" height="281" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/5ziuFEur8Vw?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe>
</div></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start">8 Exercises For A Full Body Bodyweight Workout</h2>



<p>The exercises below target different muscle groups across your body, ensuring a balanced and effective full-body workout. Combining these exercises will improve strength, stability, and flexibility, creating a well-rounded routine that challenges every part of your body.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Push-Up">Push-Up</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/push-up" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">push-up</a> is a classic bodyweight exercise that primarily targets the <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30855905/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">chest</a> and <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6251069/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">shoulders</a>. It also engages your triceps, core, and stabilizing muscles, making it a fantastic full-body movement.&nbsp;</p>



<p><a href="https://journals.lww.com/nsca-jscr/fulltext/2018/03000/Effect_of_Progressive_Calisthenic_Push_up_Training.9.aspx" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Progressive push-up training</a> has been shown to be as effective as bench press for developing upper body strength. Whereas, unlike bench presses, push-ups require no equipment, making them more accessible.&nbsp;</p>



<p>This versatile exercise can be modified for beginners or advanced athletes, ensuring it suits any fitness level.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe title="Push-Up" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/957562432?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Push-Up Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Start in a high plank position with your hands shoulder-width apart and directly under your shoulders.</li>



<li>Keep your body in a straight line from head to heels by engaging your core and glutes.</li>



<li>Lower your chest toward the floor by bending your elbows at a 45–degree angle.</li>



<li>Stop just before your chest touches the floor, then push back up to the starting position.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Maintain a neutral neck position by looking slightly ahead, not directly up or down.</li>



<li>Avoid letting your hips sag or pike; keep your body aligned for proper engagement and to protect your back.</li>



<li>Focus on slow, controlled movements to maximize muscle activation and minimize momentum. Stay engaged throughout the lowering phase instead of allowing yourself to drop.</li>



<li>If needed, modify by dropping to your knees while keeping a straight line from knees to head.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



<div class="wp-block-group medicine-table is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
<figure class="wp-block-table table-custom h-title table-border" style="font-size:16px;font-style:normal;font-weight:500"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><thead><tr><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><p class="pri-color-1">Training Style</p></th><th class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left"><p class="pri-color-1">Sets</p></th><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><p class="pri-color-1">Reps</p></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Strength Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3–5</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">3–5 (Weighted)</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Hypertrophy</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3–4</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">8–12</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Endurance Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3–4</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">15+</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Power Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3–5</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">3–5 (Explosive)</td></tr></tbody></table><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Optimal Sets &amp; Reps of Push-Up</figcaption></figure>
</div></div>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Dip">Dip</h3>



<p><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/chest-dip" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Dips</a> are a compound bodyweight exercise that effectively targets the chest and <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30725681/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">triceps</a>. They also engage the shoulders, core, and stabilizers, making them excellent for upper body strength and stability.&nbsp;</p>



<p>This exercise is versatile, as you can perform them on parallel bars, dip stations, or even sturdy furniture. Furthermore, there are many available variations of the exercise and options to change the grip. This allows you to <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/331477905_A_COMPARATIVE_ELECTROMYOGRAPHICAL_INVESTIGATION_OF_TRICEPS_BRACHII_AND_PECTORALIS_MAJOR_DURING_FOUR_DIFFERENT_FREEHAND_EXERCISES" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">vary muscle focus and adjust intensity</a> to suit your fitness level.</p>



<p>They are ideal for building pushing strength and improving muscle definition.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe title="Chest Dip" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/969666052?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Dip Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Begin by gripping parallel bars with your palms facing inward and arms fully extended.</li>



<li>Bend your elbows and lower your body until your upper arms are parallel to the floor.</li>



<li>Push through your palms to return to the starting position, fully extending your arms without locking your elbows.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>You can lean your torso slightly forward to shift focus onto your chest. Otherwise, you can keep your torso upright to focus on engaging the triceps more intensely.</li>



<li>Avoid flaring your elbows; keep them close to your body to prevent shoulder strain.</li>



<li>Keep your shoulders back and down for proper engagement and form.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Use a full range of motion, but don’t drop below parallel to protect your shoulders.</li>



<li>Beginners can use assistance bands or perform dips on a sturdy chair for support.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



<div class="wp-block-group medicine-table is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
