<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Plank">Plank</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/plank-guide" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">plank</a> is an isometric bodyweight exercise, which means it engages the muscles without moving or changing their length. This exercise engages the <a href="https://europepmc.org/article/NBK/nbk551649" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">core muscles</a> to hold the position.&nbsp;</p>



<p>The core stabilization of this exercise enhances muscular endurance and helps <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34487008/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">reduce lower back pain</a>. It also engages the shoulders, chest, back, and glutes, making it a highly effective full-body stability exercise.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Plank" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/980209730?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Plank Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Start in a forearm plank position with your elbows directly under your shoulders.</li>



<li>Extend your legs straight back, keeping your toes firmly planted and your body in a straight line.</li>



<li>Engage your core by drawing your belly button toward your spine and bracing.</li>



<li>Hold this position and maintain a steady breath throughout.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips&nbsp;</h4>



<ul>
<li>Avoid arching your back or dropping your hips, as this can reduce effectiveness and increase the risk of injury.</li>



<li>Keep your neck neutral by looking slightly ahead, not strained up or down.</li>



<li>Squeeze your glutes and thighs to maintain a strong and stable lower body.</li>
</ul>



