<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Mountain-Climber">Mountain Climber</h3>



<p><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/mountain-climber" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Mountain climbers</a> are a dynamic exercise that heavily engages the abdominal muscles. In addition, the shoulders, chest, and legs are activated throughout.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Mountain climbers and other high-intensity calisthenics also <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/357186499_Repetitive_sprint_or_calisthenics_training_which_is_more_successful_for_athletic_performance" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">improve aerobic endurance and body composition</a>. This is due to the effective combination of strength-based training with fast-paced movements.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Mountain Climbers" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/980220751?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Mountain Climber Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Begin in a high plank position with your hands directly under your shoulders.</li>



<li>Keep your body in a straight line from head to heels.</li>



<li>Drive your right knee toward your chest without letting your hips drop or rise.</li>



<li>Quickly switch legs, extending your right leg back while driving your left knee forward.</li>



<li>Continue alternating legs at a steady pace.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Avoid letting your hips sag or twist excessively; keep your core tight for stability.</li>



<li>Maintain a consistent rhythm to maximize intensity and abdominal engagement.</li>



<li>Keep your hands firmly planted and your shoulders over your wrists for support.</li>



<li>Beginners can slow the movement down to focus on form before increasing speed.</li>



<li>To make it harder, add a pause when your knee is near your chest for extra core activation.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



<div class="wp-block-group medicine-table is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
