<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Burpee">Burpee</h3>



<p>The burpee is an energetic full-body exercise that targets multiple muscle groups, including the chest, legs, core, and shoulders.&nbsp;</p>



<p>High-intensity full-body training elevates your heart rate and <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34987590/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">strengthens your cardiovascular system</a>. Burpees combine strength and cardio, making them effective for building endurance, burning calories, and improving overall fitness.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Burpees" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/980231745?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Burpee Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Stand tall with your feet shoulder-width apart and arms by your sides.</li>



<li>Squat down and place your hands on the floor in front of you.</li>



<li>Jump your feet back into a plank position.</li>



<li>Perform a push-up, lowering your chest to the floor and pushing back up.</li>



<li>Jump your feet forward to return to the squat position.</li>



<li>Explode upward into a jump, reaching your arms overhead.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Keep your core engaged to maintain a straight plank position and protect your lower back.</li>



<li>Land softly when jumping to reduce the impact on your joints.</li>



<li>Beginners can skip the push-up or jump for a lower-impact variation.</li>



<li>To increase difficulty, add a tuck jump or a second push-up before standing.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



