</div></div>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Best Full Body Bodyweight Routine</h2>



<p>This <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/workouts/bodyweight-workout-plan" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">bodyweight workout plan</a> is designed to target all major muscle groups, building strength, endurance, and balance. The <a href="https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC7927075/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">routine</a> combines dynamic and static movements to challenge your muscles and improve functional fitness. Perform this workout 2–3 times per week, allowing <a href="https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s00421-017-3725-7" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">48–72 hours</a> in between for proper recovery. Remember to include a <a href="https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s40279-017-0797-9" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">dynamic warm-up</a> before starting to <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33188962/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">reduce injury risk</a> and finish with a cooldown to aid recovery.</p>



